<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1155,1216,1311]" box="[160,285,1216,1242]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1155,1216,1311]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">The species name refers to the greyish yellow median abdominal band in the preserved male specimen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1156,1355,1520]" box="[160,276,1355,1381]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1156,1355,1520]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
The species is distinguishable from other congeners by the greyish pale yellow median band of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[374,465,1425,1450]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)), oval bulbus with well-developed posterior lobe, long, thin embolus (
<figureCitation box="[275,382,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d), 
<figureCitation box="[426,532,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a)), small RTA with a sharpened point (
<figureCitation box="[995,1102,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d,e), 
<figureCitation box="[160,264,1495,1520]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a,b)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="2782" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1156,1564,1728]" box="[160,294,1564,1590]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1156,1564,1728]" lastBlockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="2782" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">
Male: Medium-sized spider. In ethanol-preserved specimens, prosoma brown and covered with greyish white blotches laterally (
<figureCitation box="[575,666,1634,1659]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2781">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)). Eye field rather elevated. Fovea distinct. ALEs, PMES and PLEs covered with black rings. Prosoma high, sloping posteriorly. Chelicerae brown, yellowish brown fangs. Sternum oval, yellowish brown centrally, edges brown (
<figureCitation box="[326,422,142,167]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b)). Posterior margin of prosoma blackish brown, steep, slightly truncated. Leg I dark brown, rather robust, elongated, dense black bristles on patella, tibia metatarsus I, others brown with yellowish brown banding pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
Abdomen oval, smaller and narrower than prosoma, tapering posteriorly. Dorsum blackish grey with broad, greyish pale yellow median band dispersed with grey dots (
<figureCitation box="[168,259,316,341]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)). Ventrum greyish yellow with a dark grey median band comprising four rows of greyish brown dots from epigastric furrow to spinnerets (
<figureCitation box="[883,981,350,375]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b)). Spinnerets greyish brown. Measurements: TL 5.98, AL 2.86, AW 1.69, PL 3.12, PW 2.34.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,142,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">
Yellowish brown palp. Moderately long cymbium with narrowest distal region. Embolus thin, long originating from posterior portion of the bulbus and partially surrounding it (
<figureCitation box="[167,267,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d), 
<figureCitation box="[305,404,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1071,1094]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,143,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-124@19.[166,1149,142,1040]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b), a. Palp, ventral view. (b). retrolateral view. Abbreviations: e = embolus; dcrta = dorsal curve of rta; sd = sperm duct; plt = posterior lobe of tegulum; t = tegulum; vcrta = ventral curve of rta. Scale bars: (a–d) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405259/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 9</figureCitation>
(a)).Bulbus oval with a large posterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[875,975,489,514]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1674,1697]" captionTargetBox="[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-11@18.[210,1106,142,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 8. Colopsus cinerea sp. nov. (a, b). Male habitus,(a). dorsal view.(b). ventral view.(c–e). Male palp, (c). prolateral view. (d). ventral view. (e). retrolateral view. Scale bars: (a, b) = 1 mm, (c–e) = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5405257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5405257/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2782">Figures 8</figureCitation>
(d,e), 
